ER","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Source Repository\n\nhttps://github.com/dwisiswant0/next-16.2.4-pocs\n\n## CVE\n\nCVE-2026-44577\n\n## Notes\n\nDenial of Service in the Next.js Image Optimization API on self-hosted deployments. The /_next/image endpoint fetches local images into memory with no size limit. Attacker requests large local assets matching images.localPatterns to cause out-of-memory conditions. CVSS 5.9 (Medium). Vercel-hosted deployments not affected. No known active exploitation. Fixed in Next.js 15.5.16 / 16.2.5. Part of Next.js/React May 2026 security release batch.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/intelseclab/poc-archive/issues/56/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/intelseclab/poc-archive/issues/56/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/vinext/issues/1325","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/vinext","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/vinext/issues/1325/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/vinext/issues/1325/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/vinext/issues/1325/events","html_url":"https://github.com/cloudflare/vinext/issues/1325","id":4484873128,"node_id":"I_kwDORXYnQM8AAAABC1G7qA","number":1325,"title":"Treat `next/root-params` as stable: drop `experimental.rootParams` requirement and warn on deprecated flag","user":{"login":"github-actions[bot]","id":41898282,"node_id":"MDM6Qm90NDE4OTgyODI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/in/15368?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D","html_url":"https://github.com/apps/github-actions","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/received_events","type":"Bot","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":10513050976,"node_id":"LA_kwDORXYnQM8AAAACcqBtYA","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/vinext/labels/nextjs-tracking","name":"nextjs-tracking","color":"0075ca","default":false,"description":"Tracking issue for a Next.js canary change relevant to vinext"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-20T09:04:28Z","updated_at":"2026-05-22T08:12:11Z","closed_at":"2026-05-22T08:12:11Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Summary\n\nNext.js has promoted root params to a stable feature. The `experimental.rootParams` flag has been removed from `ExperimentalConfig`, and `next/root-params` is now available by default. Users who still pass `experimental.rootParams` get a deprecation warning telling them to remove it.\n\n## Upstream\n\n- Commit: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/commit/079df0f6f4bb242cd92b2c64c4a76d10986373ac\n- PR: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/93863\n\n## What changed\n\n- `experimental.rootParams` removed from `ExperimentalConfig` (`packages/next/src/server/config-shared.ts`).\n- New deprecation warning in `packages/next/src/server/config.ts`:\n\n  > `experimental.rootParams` is no longer needed, because `next/root-params` is available by default.\n\n- Type generation for root params (`.next/types/root-params.d.ts`) is no longer gated on the experimental flag or `cacheComponents` — it always runs.\n- Build/typecheck pipeline (`build/index.ts`, `build/type-check.ts`, `cli/next-typegen.ts`, `writeAppTypeDeclarations.ts`, etc.) no longer branches on the flag.\n- Limitations called out in the PR description: rootParams still cannot be used in route handlers or Server Actions; this will be expanded later.\n\n## Impact on vinext\n\nvinext already shims `next/root-params` (#806). With this change, the shim should be considered stable and unconditionally available — no config flag gating. Concrete follow-ups:\n\n1. Ensure `next/root-params` resolves regardless of any `experimental.rootParams` setting in `next.config`.\n2. If we currently check `experimental.rootParams` anywhere in the plugin or routing scanners, drop the check.\n3. Emit a deprecation warning (matching Next.js wording) when a user's `next.config` still sets `experimental.rootParams`, so users get parity guidance when migrating.\n4. If/when vinext grows a typegen story, generate `root-params.d.ts` unconditionally for App Router apps with root-level dynamic segments.\n5. Mirror the documented limitations (no rootParams in route handlers or Server Actions) in vinext's implementation/tests.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/vinext/issues/1325/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/vin