uthor_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Context\nNext.js published GHSA-c4j6-fc7j-m34r / CVE-2026-44578, a CVSS 8.6 SSRF issue in self-hosted apps using the built-in Node.js server and WebSocket upgrade handling. Official advisory: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/security/advisories/GHSA-c4j6-fc7j-m34r\n\nOfficial affected ranges:\n- `>=13.4.13 <15.5.16`\n- `>=16.0.0 <16.2.5`\n\nOfficial patched minimums are `15.5.16` and `16.2.5`. Current npm patch targets checked during triage are `15.5.18` and `16.2.6`.\n\nImportant: npm's green package/version icon is package provenance/verification. It is not proof that a version is safe for this CVE. Use the advisory ranges above as the source of truth.\n\n## This repo\n- Current `next`: `16.1.6` in dependencies and lockfile\n- Current `eslint-config-next`: `16.1.6`\n- Target: `next@16.2.6`, `eslint-config-next@16.2.6`\n- Deployment notes: `vercel.json` is present and Vercel-hosted production is not affected by the SSRF advisory, but the repo is still pinned to an affected version for self-hosted/local `next start` and future non-Vercel deployments. Vercel project list shows `plotlink` with production URL `https://plotlink.xyz`.\n\n## Suggested patch\n```bash\nnpm install --save-exact next@16.2.6 eslint-config-next@16.2.6\n```\n\n## Verification\nRun from repo root:\n```bash\nnpm audit --omit=dev\nnpm run lint\nnpm run typecheck\nnpm run test\nnpm run build\n```\n\nRun `npm run test:e2e` if the Playwright environment is available. Smoke cron/API paths in `vercel.json`: `/api/cron/backfill`, `/api/cron/airdrop-price`, `/api/cron/airdrop-weekly`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- `package.json` and `package-lock.json` resolve `next` to `16.2.6`.\n- `npm audit --omit=dev` no longer reports GHSA-c4j6-fc7j-m34r for `next`.\n- Build and core tests pass.\n- Create a Vercel preview first; promote to production only after smoke checks.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/realproject7/plotlink/issues/1210/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/realproject7/plotlink/issues/1210/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Gabiribpin/circlehood-booking/issues/655","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Gabiribpin/circlehood-booking","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Gabiribpin/circlehood-booking/issues/655/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Gabiribpin/circlehood-booking/issues/655/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Gabiribpin/circlehood-booking/issues/655/events","html_url":"https://github.com/Gabiribpin/circlehood-booking/issues/655","id":4419805050,"node_id":"I_kwDOROu4is8AAAABB3Dfeg","number":655,"title":"Remover workaround NFT quando Next/Vercel corrigirem incompatibilidade Turbopack middleware","user":{"login":"Gabiribpin","id":163570738,"node_id":"U_kgDOCb_kMg","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/163570738?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabiribpin","html_url":"https://github.com/Gabiribpin","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabiribpin/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabiribpin/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabiribpin/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabiribpin/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabiribpin/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabiribpin/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabiribpin/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabiribpin/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.